{"id": 232064952, "title": "Ruth Langsford leads tributes to Michael Mosley after body found in search", "text": "Ruth Langsford and a number of other celebrities are sharing tributes to and memories of presenter Michael Mosley, as a body has been found in the search for the TV personality. The TV and radio presenter - known for appearing on television programmes like This Morning and The One Show - went missing last week, vanishing on Wednesday after going for a walk while on holiday on the Greek island of Symi. According to the BBC a new breakthrough has been made in the search and rescue mission led by authorities in the area. His wife, Dr Clare Mosley has made a statement, sharing her devastation. Read more: A body has been found in the search for TV presenter Michael Mosley Read more: Fern Britton hints at ITV This Morning return and opens up about marriage breakdown She says: \"I don't know quite where to begin with this. It's devastating to have lost Michael, my wonderful, funny, kind and brilliant husband. We had an incredibly lucky life together. We loved each other very much and were so happy together. I am incredibly proud of our children, their resilience and support over the past days. \"My family and I have been hugely comforted by the outpouring of love from people from around the world. It's clear that Michael meant a huge amount to so many of you. \"We're taking comfort in the fact that he so very nearly made it. He did an incredible climb, took the wrong route and collapsed where he couldn\u2019t be easily seen by the extensive search team. \"Michael was an adventurous man, it's part of what made him so special. We are so grateful to the extraordinary people on Symi who have worked tirelessly to help find him. Some of these people on the island, who hadn't even heard of Michael, worked from dawn till dusk unasked. We're also very grateful to the press who have dealt with us with great respect. \"I feel so lucky to have our children and my amazing friends. Most of all, I feel so lucky to have had this life with Michael. Thank you all.\" Those who have worked with him over the years have led tributes to him this morning. Posting to her Instagram feed, Ruth Langsford wrote: \"So terribly sad to hear the news of Doctor Michael Mosley\u2019s death. He was a brilliant and utterly charming man. My condolences and love to his family.\" Fellow television doctor, Amir Khan, who often stars on the likes of Lorraine and Good Morning Britain, said: \"This is so sad, he was such a lovely gentle caring man,\" complete with a red heartbroken emoji. Jamie Oliver wrote via Instagram: \"Rest in peace Michael Mosley\u2026. Absolutely devastating news about the sad loss of fellow tv presenter Micheal Mosley today.\" Peter Andre also shared a tribute too, saying \"absolutely devastating. A wonderful human being. Ulrika Jonsson said: \"Such tragic news. What lovely, lovely man. Thinking of his family.\" Michael Mosley is survived by his wife, their three sons, Alex, Jack and Daniel, and a daughter, Kate.", "summary": "The BBC and This Morning doctor vanished on Wednesday after going for a walk while on holiday on the Greek island of Symi, and a body has been found amid the search and rescue operation launched by authorities in the area", "url": "https://www.rsvplive.ie/news/celebs/ruth-langsford-leads-tributes-michael-32992962", "image": "https://i2-prod.rsvplive.ie/authors/sarah-magliocco/article32992940.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_Michael-Mosley.png", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 15:19:05", "author": "Sarah Magliocco", "authors": ["Sarah Magliocco"], "language": "en", "source_country": "ie", "sentiment": 0.639}